.TH "RYTH" "1"
.SH NAME
ryth \- Scriptable iwd interface
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B ryth
<command> [options]
.SH DESCRIPTION
ryth is a scriptable interface to the iwd wifi backend.
All output is JSON. Designed for use in scripts and automation widgets.
Device and station are selected automatically.
.SH "STATUS"
.B ryth status
 [\-\-watch] [\-\-help]
.PP
Current wifi status (state, signal, powered, etc.)
.PP
\fBOptions:\fR
.TP
\fB\-\-watch\fR
Stream updates on change
.TP
\fB\-h, \-\-help\fR
Print help
.SH "LIST"
.B ryth list
 [\-\-watch] [\-\-help]
.PP
List discovered networks (cached)
.PP
\fBOptions:\fR
.TP
\fB\-\-watch\fR
Re-output on each scan cycle
.TP
\fB\-h, \-\-help\fR
Print help
.SH "SCAN"
.B ryth scan
 [\-\-help]
.PP
Trigger a scan and return updated network list
.PP
\fBOptions:\fR
.TP
\fB\-h, \-\-help\fR
Print help
.SH "CONNECT"
.B ryth connect
 <SSID> [\-\-password <PASSWORD>] [\-\-help]
.PP
Connect to a network by SSID
.PP
\fBOptions:\fR
.TP
\fB\-\-password\fR <PASSWORD>

.TP
\fB\-h, \-\-help\fR
Print help
.SH "DISCONNECT"
.B ryth disconnect
 [\-\-help]
.PP
Disconnect from the current network
.PP
\fBOptions:\fR
.TP
\fB\-h, \-\-help\fR
Print help
.SH "AUTOCONNECT"
.B ryth autoconnect
 <SSID> <STATE> [\-\-help]
.PP
Toggle autoconnect for a known network
.PP
\fBOptions:\fR
.TP
\fB\-h, \-\-help\fR
Print help
.SH "FORGET"
.B ryth forget
 <SSID> [\-\-help]
.PP
Forget a known network
.PP
\fBOptions:\fR
.TP
\fB\-h, \-\-help\fR
Print help
.SH "KNOWN"
.B ryth known
 [\-\-help]
.PP
List known networks
.PP
\fBOptions:\fR
.TP
\fB\-h, \-\-help\fR
Print help
.SH "POWER"
.B ryth power
 <STATE> [\-\-help]
.PP
Toggle wifi power
.PP
\fBOptions:\fR
.TP
\fB\-h, \-\-help\fR
Print help
.SH OUTPUT
All commands output JSON to stdout. Errors are printed to stderr as:
.PP
{"error": "message"}
